@echo off
TITLE Ryan's Custom Party Hat Maker V.1 made by Ryan
:start
cls




Echo.
Echo Welcome to Ryans Custom Party Hat Maker V.1
Echo .
Echo (Dont forget to download the README.txt file from the thread.)
Echo .
Echo 1. If you want a curtain colour for your Party Hat..... Press 1
Echo .
Echo 2. If you want your party hat to be the same texture as an armour....Press 2
Echo .
SET /P Type=What Type?   


if %Type%==1 GOTO colours
if %Type%==2 GOTO textures



:colours
cls
Echo .
Echo Choose your colour.......
Echo .
Echo .
Echo .
Echo Black
Echo .
Echo Gold
Echo .
Echo Dull Green (type dull for this option)
Echo.
SET /P Colour=What colour do you want?    

if %Colour%==black GOTO black
if %Colour%==gold GOTO gold
if %Colour%==dull GOTO dull








:black
cls
Echo if(i == 6992){  //~Black party hat~
Echo class8.aStringArray189 = new String[5];
Echo class8.aStringArray189[1] = "Wear";
Echo class8.anIntArray156 = new int[1];
Echo class8.anIntArray160 = new int [1];
Echo //Purple: 926-127
Echo class8.anIntArray156[0] = 926;
Echo class8.anIntArray160[0] = 6;
Echo class8.anInt174 = 2635;//Item Look
Echo class8.anInt181 = 440;
Echo class8.anInt190 = 76;
Echo class8.anInt198 = 1850;
Echo class8.anInt204 = 0;
Echo class8.anInt169 = 1;
Echo class8.anInt194 = 1;
Echo class8.anInt165 = 187;
Echo class8.anInt200 = 363;
Echo class8.anInt175 = 29;
Echo class8.anInt197 = 87;
Echo class8.aString170 = "Black Party hat";
Echo class8.aByteArray178 = "A Black Party Hat".getBytes();
Echo }
Echo .
Echo  .
Echo  .
Echo  .
Echo  Copy and paste this into your CLASS8.JAVA and then use pickup or watever to get item.
Echo  .
Echo  .
Echo  .
SET /P New=Do You Want To Make Another Party Hat (y/n)?
If %New%==y GOTO start
If %New%==n GOTO end
